title: Bellevue rolls to win over Truckers
text:
Bellevue rolls to win over Truckers 12:32 a.m. EDT October 10, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Bellevue 50, Norwalk 0 
Bellevue coach Ed Nasonti won the 199th game of his coaching career as the Redmen rolled to a Northen Ohio League win over Norwalk. 
Bryce Ray scored three touchdowns, including a pair of rushing scores and a 61-yard punt return for touchdown. Alec Foos also scored twice on rushing touchdowns. 
The Redmen improve to 5-2 overall, 3-0 in the NOL. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1Ln1A7Q TOP VIDEOS
